COPS have arrested two people suspected to be behind truck hijackings and armed robberies in Joburg. The suspects, who were found in possession of two unlicensed firearms, were arrested in Joburg City Centre on Thursday, 24 February. Lieutenant Colonel Mavela Masondo said cops had been searching for suspects involved in truck hijackings and robberies, and information led them to a flat where they were residing. He said upon searching the suspects and premises, police found two firearms and a signal jammer. “Both suspects were arrested and charged with possession of unlicensed firearms and a signal jammer. The firearms will be sent for ballistic tests, and suspects will be profiled to establish links to other serious and violent crimes,” Masondo added. The suspects are expected to appear in the Johannesburg Magistrates Court on Monday, 28 February.